title._content: RAUPO with sails set and underway

description._content:
RAUPO, formerly the LOUISA CRAIG, was built at Kinghorn in Fifeshire in 1876. The vessel was a sister ship to JAMES CRAIG which now resides with the Sydney Heritage Fleet.

This photo is part of the Australian National Maritime Museum’s William Hall collection. The Hall collection combines photographs from both William J Hall and his father William Frederick Hall. 

The Australian National Maritime Museum undertakes research and accepts public comments that enhance the information we hold about images in our collection. If you can identify a person, vessel or landmark, write the details in the Comments box below. 

Thank you for helping caption this important historical image.

Object number: ANMS1092[010]
